# C++ Style

## Optional access

After checking `optional.has_value()`, use `.value()` to read the contents. Do not use `*` or `->`.

```cpp
// BAD
if (metadata.has_value()) {
    take.durationMs = metadata->durationMs;
}

// GOOD
if (metadata.has_value()) {
    take.durationMs = metadata.value().durationMs;
}
```

Additional style rules may be added here over time.
